<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1711,2036]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,311,1711,1737]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
The record below from 
<collectingCountry box="[593,720,1712,1738]" name="Guatemala" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
is a considerable extension of the previously known distribution of this species, 
<collectingCountry box="[391,549,1749,1775]" name="United States of America" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[567,666,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[680,802,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[815,927,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[941,1028,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="Kansas" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Kansas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1042,1198,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1212,1337,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="Oklahoma" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Oklahoma</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1351,1423,1749,1775]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Texas</collectingRegion>
), which was mapped by 
<bibRefCitation author="Foote, R. H. &amp; Blanc, F. L. &amp; Norrbom, A. L." box="[419,639,1786,1812]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref41610" refString="Foote, R. H., Blanc, F. L. &amp; Norrbom, A. L. (1993) Handbook of the fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) of America north of Mexico. Comstock Publishing Associates, Ithaca. xii + 571 p." type="book" year="1993">Foote et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1711,2036]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,298,1823,1849]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Biology.</emphasis>
The only previously reported host plants for 
<taxonomicName box="[834,1017,1824,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Trupanea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudovicina">
<emphasis box="[834,1017,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">T. pseudovicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are 
<taxonomicName authority="(Benth.) Greene (Wasbauer 1972)" authorityName="Greene (Wasbauer" authorityYear="1972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Bebbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="juncea">
<emphasis box="[1069,1238,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Bebbia juncea</emphasis>
(Benth.) Greene (
<bibRefCitation author="Wasbauer, M. S." box="[158,348,1861,1887]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref42846" refString="Wasbauer, M. S. (1972) An annotated host catalog of the fruit flies of America north of Mexico (Diptera: Tephritidae). Occasional Papers, California Department of Agriculture, Bureau of Entomology, 19, [i] + 172 p." type="book" year="1972">Wasbauer 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, considered an erroneous record by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goeden, R. D. &amp; Teerink, J. A." box="[803,1120,1861,1887]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="361 - 372" refId="ref41981" refString="Goeden, R. D. &amp; Teerink, J. A. (1998) Life history and description of immature stages of Trupanea pseudovicina Hering (Diptera: Tephritidae) on Porophyllum gracile Bentham in southern California. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 361 - 372." type="journal article" year="1998">Goeden &amp; Teerink (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Benth." authorityName="Benth." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Porophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis box="[1190,1436,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Porophyllum gracile</emphasis>
Benth.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wasbauer, M. S." box="[247,436,1898,1924]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref42846" refString="Wasbauer, M. S. (1972) An annotated host catalog of the fruit flies of America north of Mexico (Diptera: Tephritidae). Occasional Papers, California Department of Agriculture, Bureau of Entomology, 19, [i] + 172 p." type="book" year="1972">Wasbauer 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Goeden, R. D. &amp; Teerink, J. A." box="[453,753,1898,1924]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="361 - 372" refId="ref41981" refString="Goeden, R. D. &amp; Teerink, J. A. (1998) Life history and description of immature stages of Trupanea pseudovicina Hering (Diptera: Tephritidae) on Porophyllum gracile Bentham in southern California. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 361 - 372." type="journal article" year="1998">Goeden &amp; Teerink 1998</bibRefCitation>
). We reared it from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jacq.) Cass." authorityName="Cass." baseAuthorityName="Jacq." box="[1007,1436,1898,1924]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Porophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruderale">
<emphasis box="[1007,1272,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Porophyllum ruderale</emphasis>
(Jacq.) Cass.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[159,294,1936,1962]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[305,410,1936,1962]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Tageteae">Tageteae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[434,604,1936,1962]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–125" captionStartId="60.[151,269,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,188,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-36@60.[160,1445,187,1949]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 123–125. Host plants: Porophyllum ruderale, host of Trupanea pseudovicina: 123, inflorescence; 124–125, capitula." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs. 123–125</figureCitation>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[650,781,1936,1962]" name="Guatemala" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
. The larvae develop in the flowerhead.
</paragraph>
